Wallpaper installation instructions!!!! SAVE THIS POST FOR LATER! FYI I brought my best girlfriend with me to the photo shoot yo help me install the wallpaper. She said she wanted to learn…legit she came out of this experience going…”wow….that was so easy. The wallpaper is SO workable!” She was FREAKING out when it got stuck and I had to pull it apart…ALSO when there is a small gap in seam you can REALLY pull at this paper to get it to budge over! She was SHOCKED! I’ll show in stories our fun! She was cracking up over me and my sock hand!!! Ok here is your tips….NOW go WALLPAPER!!!! @coloraydecor is the BEST! This pattern is Forest Undergrowth! 

1. LAY PANELS OUT FLAT TO MAKE SURE THEY MATCH UP. 

2.  MEASURE WALLPAPER WIDTH AND MARK VERTICAL LINE IN WALL USING LEVEL. THIS MEANS WALLPAPER WILL HANG STRAIGHT..VERY IMPORTANT FOR EDGES TO MEET UP! 

3. START FROM TOP LEFT CORNER…UNPEEL AND STICK IN CORNER. SLOWLY I PEELING TOP SECTION, MAKING SURE THE RIGHT EDGE MEETS UP NICELY WITH LEVEL LINE DRAWN. 

4. PULL BACKING OUT FROM UNDERNEATH AND USING SOFT CLOTH OR SOCK 🤷‍♀️ SMOOTH OUT AIR BUBBLES AS YOU UNPEEL. 

5 THIS ON REPEAT for each panel!

Yesterday was a low day. I sometimes have those days. Days where tasks feel overwhelming….my anxiety kicks up…panic sets in…and then I usually just cry. 

Yesterdays low was triggered by finances and it progressed into feelings of inadequacy and panic. Then all the negative thoughts come in. I’m not making enough money…..I’m not as good as my Instagram peers….resentful of staying home with kids and letting go of MY career….MY goals…MY earnings! Not feeling like I’m a good enough instagrammer…and never having enough time to DO ALL I WANT!!! 

Obviously I let those UNTRUE thoughts creep in. I had to run an errand with my middle yesterday and I let her know “I’m just having a hard emotional time” “ I’m not upset with you…I just need to drive in silence is that ok?” She said yes…and I quietly cried and she gave me the space to do so. After our errand we went to the fruit stand, held hands, and enjoyed some chocolate strawberries. I’m ok with my kiddos seeing me upset…and I want to show them that it is OK to FEEL your feelings…move through it…and MOVE on. 

Who can relate to my day?!?

Once legs were secure to frame, I screwed back legs to the frame of the existing cabinet for extra support. I used a 3/4 plywood on top for quartz base.

Do you have textured drywall windows and NO trim LIKE ME?!? I found a SOLUTION…..AND…NOW I want to trim out EVERY window!!!!

Shelfie Styling TIPS!!!!! Lay all items that you want to use on floor in groupings…books…toys…art…etc. I usually like to add some greenery was well. Faux works best in kiddos rooms! 

I start by placing the larger items at the ends of the shelf’s…towards the corners. Maybe a stuffy…or a doll…a tall book that has a fun cover…or a cute neon sign like mine (Walgreens…can you believe?!) when placing your tall items in the corners be SURE to alternate the sides..left side one shelf…next shelf down  place your item on the right. This gives visual BALANCE…KEY! 

Once I have the ends of the shelf done I work towards the middle. Each shelf has a purpose…books maybe on one. I like to stack the books in interesting ways. Maybe some of the books are upright…while others lay on the side. Try to break up the space into different visual elements. In with the books I like to add a cute plant on the end…or a cute toy to break it up. 

I love the idea of storing toys that are frequently played with in the shelves. I like to place the toys in baskets so that they simply pull the basket off the shelf…play…then return once done. Baskets are great for organizing as well as adding visual interest to your shelf! 

I like to have a lot of color…so I pick books with fun covers or place artwork around for color! Don’t forget the artwork!!!! 

It’s just a balancing act….but with these tips you will be off to a good start! Any questions…ASK below!!!

My MISTAKE is your WIN! DONT start the first corner of wallpaper directly lining up to edge….YOU want to have 1-2” of overhang. 

Walls are not completely straight and sometimes the pattern angles a bit. Because I started  directly in the corner, and the wall pulled the pattern a bit sideways….so my next wallpaper panel matching up the pattern meant there was a gap in the beginning of the wallpaper and the trim. 

 I had to completely peel this first piece off and restart corner with overhang. Luckily this wallpaper is strong and came off ceiling…and re stuck in new position like a charm! Quality wallpaper MATTERS!

WALLPAPER WORST FEAR…..hands down EVERYONE says “when it sticks together…” that’s IT…

Here’s what you need to do. 

1. Stay CALM

2. Work out by starting with the outside…unpeeling itself then towards the middle, 

3. Work top to bottom. 

4. Be patient…it might take a bit….but it will unstick. 

5. Once unstick from itself…get back on wall ASAP. 

I always hear “I LOVE the look but I’m TOO scared to install wallpaper….it will stick together…and then I will never get it unstuck! I hear YOU!!!!!! After the ol’ first time cactus wallpaper install incident of 2018…where I wept in a ball on the floor…NEXT to my crumpled stuck together paper. I had spent $350 on new paper and was SURE it was the worst idea I had ever had. 

I picked myself off the floor…worked like a champ for what felt like hours…BUT just minutes…to get it unstick and on wall. And BOY that cactus room went viral….AND I always laugh in my head bc man that was STRESSFUL!!! 

I learned an important lesson that day! Don’t stress about it sticking to itself. It DOESN’T ALWAYS happen…but when it does…it’s TOTALLY going to pull apart…and that wallpaper will re stick like a champion to the wall!!!
